# Git Remotes Configuration

This repository is configured to push to two remote locations:

## Remotes:

1. **GitHub** (origin fetch + push)
   - URL: git@github.com:levysantanna/k8s-orchestrator.git
   - Public repository
   - CI/CD workflows enabled

2. **Local GitServer** (origin push)
   - URL: ssh://git@localhost:2223/git/k8s-orchestrator.git
   - Container: gitserver (port 2223)
   - Local backup and development

## Commands:

```bash
# Push to both remotes at once (default behavior)
git push origin main

# Push to GitHub only
git push git@github.com:levysantanna/k8s-orchestrator.git main

# Push to local gitserver only
git push local main

# View all remotes
git remote -v
```

## Setup:

```bash
# Add local gitserver as remote
git remote add local ssh://git@localhost:2223/git/k8s-orchestrator.git

# Configure origin to push to both
git remote set-url --add --push origin git@github.com:levysantanna/k8s-orchestrator.git
git remote set-url --add --push origin ssh://git@localhost:2223/git/k8s-orchestrator.git
```

## GitServer Container:

- **Container**: gitserver
- **SSH Port**: 2223
- **User**: git
- **Repositories Path**: /git/
- **Status**: Check with `docker ps --filter "name=git"`

## Benefits:

✅ Automatic dual backup on every push
✅ Local copy always available (even offline)
✅ GitHub for CI/CD and public access
✅ GitServer for private local development
